	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well, if you go to <!-- w --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.grandtheftendo.com">www.grandtheftendo.com</a><!-- w --> , there's a box that says "news" and it says below "neshla has been released" and then below all that stuff in the same box, it says "view". click that, scroll down, and there's what he calls the neshla users manual, and if you read through that, you should get a general idea of everything. And also, look at the .H files to see exactly what each macro does. personally, I think NESHLA is too complicated. It should not take 5 seperate files, not including h files, to make the Hello world program. I just don't see how that made grandtheftendo any easier to develope. I use NESASM for now.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
